  "text": "The Chromium multi-process architecture is defined across five key files in the content module:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h, line 195): The browser-side representation of a renderer process. This class implements the RenderProcessHost interface and manages communication with renderer processes, including IPC channels and Mojo interfaces for browser-to-renderer control messages.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (content/browser/browser_main_loop.h, line 106): The main event loop of the browser process. This class orchestrates the initialization and shutdown of the browser's main thread, managing critical components like media managers, audio systems, and the message loop that processes all browser events.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h, line 126): The main thread implementation in renderer processes where WebView instances live. This class inherits from both RenderThread and ChildThreadImpl, implementing the mojom::Renderer interface to handle messages from the browser process.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (content/browser/child_process_launcher.h, line 212): Responsible for asynchronously launching child processes. This class manages the creation of renderer and other child processes, handling platform-specific process launching logic and notifying clients when processes are ready.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer** (content/common/renderer.mojom, line 49): The IPC/Mojo interface definition for browser-to-renderer communication. This interface defines the protocol for channel-associated messages that maintain FIFO ordering with respect to legacy IPC messages, serving as the primordial interface for renderer process communication.\n\nThese files form the core of Chromium's multi-process architecture, with the browser process (BrowserMainLoop) spawning renderer processes (ChildProcessLauncher) and communicating with them through RenderProcessHostImpl on the browser side and RenderThreadImpl on the renderer side, using the Renderer Mojo interface."
}

